          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the tangzhong, cool",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "See the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "tangzhong",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp87lf5i0000agv4x1wj3r3q"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " method. Whisk 30 g {{strong-bread-flour}} with 150 ml {{whole-milk}} in a small pan over medium heat, stirring until it thickens to a smooth paste. Cool to room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough, bulk ferment 90 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine 320 g {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{yeast-dried}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} in a large bowl or stand mixer. Add the cooled tangzhong, 100 ml warm {{whole-milk}}, and beaten {{eggs}}. Mix to a shaggy dough, then knead for 10 minutes by hand or 7 minutes in a stand mixer. Add the soft {{unsalted-butter}} in small pieces, continuing to knead until the dough is smooth and elastic. Shape into a ball, cover, and bulk ferment for 90 minutes until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape, proof, and bake 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the dough into 4 equal pieces. Shape each into a round ball and place side by side in a greased 900 g loaf tin. Cover and proof for 60 minutes until the dough crowns above the rim. Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Brush the top with any remaining beaten egg or milk. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until deep gold. The internal temperature should reach 88 to 90°C. Cool in the tin for 10 minutes, then turn out and cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
